Selling <i>beaucoup amour</i>

28:15.600 --> 28:20.117
No. No, you won't.

28:24.240 --> 28:26.277
How would you like...?

28:27.160 --> 28:28.879
How would I like...?

28:30.000 --> 28:33.437
How would you like staying with me?

28:33.560 --> 28:35.791
It feels right like this

28:35.920 --> 28:38.355
So that's how we should be

28:39.480 --> 28:41.551
So, would you like?

28:41.680 --> 28:43.000
Yes, I would like

28:43.120 --> 28:47.592
OK, it's set, no more to say

28:47.720 --> 28:49.837
Screw the Engineer!

28:49.960 --> 28:53.715
You're the one good thing
that I've found out here

28:59.120 --> 29:04.195
You are sunlight

29:04.320 --> 29:07.631
And I, moon

29:07.760 --> 29:13.279
Joined by the gods of fortune

29:13.400 --> 29:18.759
Midnight and high noon

29:18.880 --> 29:23.159
Sharing the sky

29:24.440 --> 29:28.070
One and the same

29:28.240 --> 29:32.519
You and I

29:33.600 --> 29:37.913
You are here

29:38.040 --> 29:41.112
Like a mystery

29:41.240 --> 29:44.358
I'm from a world

29:44.480 --> 29:52.195
That's so different
from all that you are

29:54.080 --> 29:59.200
How in the light of one night

29:59.320 --> 30:04.395
Did we come so far?

30:04.520 --> 30:10.915
Outside, day starts to dawn

30:11.040 --> 30:17.037
Your moon still floats on high

30:17.160 --> 30:20.710
- The birds awake
- And the stars shine true

30:20.880 --> 30:24.874
- My hands still shake
- I reach for you

30:25.000 --> 30:31.236
And we meet in the sky

30:56.880 --> 31:02.478
You are sunlight

31:03.040 --> 31:06.192
And I, moon

31:06.320 --> 31:09.757
Joined here

31:09.880 --> 31:13.840
Brightening the sky

31:13.960 --> 31:16.953
With the flame

31:19.280 --> 31:22.398
Of love

31:23.560 --> 31:31.400
We are sunlight

31:31.520 --> 31:38.518
Moonlight

31:39.920 --> 31:41.957
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDS AND CHEERS)

31:50.600 --> 31:54.640
(LAUGHS)
Tomorrow night will be the full moon

31:56.680 --> 31:59.991
I can bring friends to bless our love

32:00.120 --> 32:01.839
(CHUCKLES) OK.

32:01.960 --> 32:04.759
With paper dragons and perfume

32:06.440 --> 32:08.193
If you want me to

32:08.880 --> 32:10.633
- Dragons?
- Yes.

32:10.760 --> 32:11.876
Sure.

32:23.160 --> 32:25.595
John, is that you, buddy?
Listen to me

32:25.720 --> 32:28.519
Do I sound different?
That's how it should be

32:28.640 --> 32:32.714
Last night,
I spent a whole lifetime in paradise

32:32.840 --> 32:35.560
Tell the CO I'm taking all of my leave

32:35.720 --> 32:39.839
We're going to play house,
John, it's like Christmas Eve

32:39.960 --> 32:44.716
We have sworn
we won't see the sun for 48 hours

32:44.840 --> 32:47.230
JOHN: What are you saying?
Are you out of your mind?

32:47.400 --> 32:50.632
All leave is canceled,
you could be left behind

32:50.760 --> 32:53.355
Saigon is falling apart
and you'd better be here

32:53.480 --> 32:55.790
MAN: Please have your papers ready!

32:55.920 --> 32:58.560
JOHN: Here is the news
since you've been on the moon

32:58.680 --> 33:01.434
Cities in the boondocks
are dropping like flies

33:01.560 --> 33:03.756
Wives and civilians
will be shipping out soon

33:03.880 --> 33:06.714
Crowds around the embassy
have tears in their eyes

33:06.840 --> 33:09.958
Thieu has resigned,
the new regime may not hold

33:10.080 --> 33:12.436
People at the palace
think we'll send the Marines

33:12.560 --> 33:15.394
We are sending nothing
from what I've been told

33:15.520 --> 33:16.715
- Buddy, are you there?
- Yes!

33:16.840 --> 33:21.790
Do you know what that means?
Sure, time to fall in love!

33:21.920 --> 33:25.072
John, listen fast,
you did not get this call

33:25.200 --> 33:27.874
You're the one
who bought the girl for me, after all

33:28.000 --> 33:30.993
Once you are a friend,
you're a friend through and through

33:31.120 --> 33:33.555
When you were in trouble, man,
I covered for you

33:33.680 --> 33:37.037
Not this time,
the town's too hot for one Kongai whore

33:37.200 --> 33:39.954
Ol' buddy, I will not get you killed

33:40.120 --> 33:42.760
She is no whore, all right?
You saw her too

33:42.880 --> 33:45.873
She's really more like... the April moon

33:46.040 --> 33:48.714
- April fucking moon?
- Both her parents died

33:48.880 --> 33:51.349
She was all alone, she was terrified

33:51.480 --> 33:55.360
Sweet as that and she's an orphan too
How can a guy fight that?

33:55.480 --> 33:57.711
You've got one day, not two,
then be back

34:00.120 --> 34:01.793
- Monsieur Chris, you're late.
- Shit!

34:01.920 --> 34:04.640
What, she kept you up all night?

34:04.760 --> 34:07.753
We had a deal for Kim, but that's on ice

34:07.880 --> 34:10.634
I'm sorry, Sergeant,
but I've changed the price

34:10.760 --> 34:11.989
What do you mean?

34:12.120 --> 34:15.033
I need a visa from your embassy

34:15.159 --> 34:17.675
Hey? You give me that,
you get the girl for free

34:17.800 --> 34:20.759
Look, cut the crap,
this money's all I've got

34:20.880 --> 34:23.395
I don't give visas out,
is this a deal or not?

34:23.520 --> 34:26.114
- You tell me
- Ah, shit

34:26.239 --> 34:28.800
- OK, OK, the money, it will do
- Down

34:28.960 --> 34:31.953
Too bad, I had a Rolex watch for you,
it's yours, take it.

34:32.080 --> 34:34.993
I'll get my papers in another way.

34:35.120 --> 34:39.239
I'll make a rich man
of some attaché, you asshole!

34:39.360 --> 34:42.717
With little shits like him,
you take the bucks and run

34:42.840 --> 34:45.958
He gave me six weeks' income,
I'll be gone in one

34:46.080 --> 34:48.675
I'll castrate you
next time I see you, you little fuck.

34:48.800 --> 34:50.837
(WOMEN CHATTER EXCITEDLY)

34:55.159 --> 34:59.234
One of us girls is moving on

34:59.360 --> 35:03.752
One girl will get out of Saigon

35:03.880 --> 35:06.076
So look who's really Miss Saigon

35:06.200 --> 35:08.317
She'll leave this wasted life behind

35:08.440 --> 35:11.512
She'll live the movie in my mind

35:11.640 --> 35:12.640
MAN: They're here!

35:13.880 --> 35:16.236
- Shh!
- ALL: Surprise!

35:16.360 --> 35:18.477
Look how he bought her a new dress

35:18.600 --> 35:20.592
You did a job on him, I guess

35:20.760 --> 35:22.956
He simply asked me, I said "yes"

35:23.080 --> 35:24.116
GIRL: Yeah, right

35:25.080 --> 35:28.073
Come on, let's bless the new princess

35:28.200 --> 35:30.795
(GIRLS CHATTER)

35:33.080 --> 35:34.992
CHRIS: Yeah, that's me. Get off.

35:35.120 --> 35:37.919
Hey! Shoes off.

35:45.920 --> 35:51.678
<i>Dju vui vay</i>

35:52.480 --> 35:58.112
<i>Vju doi may</i>

35:59.160 --> 36:04.997
<i>Dju vui vay</i>

36:05.600 --> 36:10.994
<i>Vao nyay may</i>

36:14.480 --> 36:20.397
Will you who gave me life smile today?

36:20.520 --> 36:25.390
Look with favoring eyes on this man

36:25.520 --> 36:31.437
Show your daughter's heart
your forgiveness

36:31.560 --> 36:37.158
And send to us from your home above

36:37.280 --> 36:44.596
Your blessing on our love

36:46.400 --> 36:49.837
<i>Dju vui vay</i>

36:50.320 --> 36:53.358
<i>Dju vui vay</i>

36:53.520 --> 36:59.869
<i>Vju doi may</i>

37:00.000 --> 37:06.315
<i>Dju vui vay</i>

37:06.440 --> 37:10.639
<i>Vao nyay may</i>

37:12.840 --> 37:16.277
<i>Dju vui vay</i>

37:16.400 --> 37:19.279
It's pretty, but what does it mean?

37:19.880 --> 37:22.349
<i>Vju doi may</i>

37:22.480 --> 37:26.360
It's what all the girls sing at weddings

37:26.480 --> 37:32.033
- What?
- They didn't know what else to sing

37:32.160 --> 37:35.039
<i>Vao nyay may</i>

37:35.160 --> 37:39.279
It's the prettiest thing
that I have ever heard

37:39.440 --> 37:41.636
(GIRLS TALK EXCITEDLY)

37:58.640 --> 38:00.393
Hey, girls!

38:02.280 --> 38:06.194
- To Miss Saigon.
- ALL: Miss Saigon!

38:09.160 --> 38:11.277
You're here, at last

38:11.400 --> 38:13.596
I've come to take you home

38:13.720 --> 38:17.600
I hid all night,
I tunneled through the line

38:17.720 --> 38:21.475
Kim, come with me,
we'll flee this shameful place

38:21.600 --> 38:24.957
They're done, we'll win,
you're safe and you are mine

38:25.080 --> 38:27.151
- Hey! This girl is mine
- Yours?

38:27.320 --> 38:28.720
- Now who are you?
- KIM: Stop

38:28.840 --> 38:31.435
Who is this man, this American pig

38:31.560 --> 38:34.792
Who I now find with you in this place?

38:34.920 --> 38:37.992
Why are you here
with these flea-bitten whores?

38:38.120 --> 38:39.839
Do you wear the same paint on your face?

38:40.000 --> 38:43.232
- Get out!
- You have no right to be here

38:43.360 --> 38:46.080
I'm not a prize you can claim

38:46.200 --> 38:48.760
We were promised at 13

38:48.880 --> 38:51.634
The woman I've become is not the same

38:51.760 --> 38:53.717
Our fathers bound us together

38:53.840 --> 38:55.194
Why couldn't you wait?

38:55.320 --> 38:57.755
You knew I'd come back to get you!
It isn't too late

38:57.880 --> 39:00.600
My parents got themselves killed
in the week you changed sides

39:00.720 --> 39:04.509
If there were promises,
all of them died when they died

39:04.640 --> 39:06.154
Show's over, pal.

39:06.320 --> 39:08.551
(GIRLS SCREAM)

39:08.680 --> 39:11.070
- Kim, leave this man behind
- Stay here

39:11.240 --> 39:13.709
No! Go on

39:13.840 --> 39:15.513
And shoot!

39:15.640 --> 39:18.872
I will not change my mind

39:19.040 --> 39:22.158
- You are still mine
- Not anymore

39:22.280 --> 39:25.956
- You're mine until we die
- Get off of her!

39:26.080 --> 39:29.790
Saigon is doomed

39:29.920 --> 39:32.196
And so is your GI

39:32.320 --> 39:33.879
She'll leave with me

39:34.000 --> 39:38.438
You broke your father's word

39:38.600 --> 39:43.311
This is your curse

39:59.560 --> 40:00.789
Get out!

40:00.960 --> 40:02.633
(SHOUTS IN VIETNAMESE)

40:07.280 --> 40:09.078
CHRIS: What a party that was

40:11.080 --> 40:13.720
You're going to leave me now

40:14.440 --> 40:16.796
Yes, I'm going to leave

40:17.800 --> 40:21.794
And take you out with me

40:30.960 --> 40:35.637
In a place that won't let us feel

40:35.760 --> 40:40.312
In a life where nothing seems real

40:40.440 --> 40:42.955
I have found you

40:44.840 --> 40:49.039
I have found you

40:51.520 --> 40:55.992
In a world that's moving too fast

40:56.120 --> 40:59.591
In a world where nothing can last

40:59.720 --> 41:02.519
I will hold you

41:04.480 --> 41:07.314
I will hold you

41:07.480 --> 41:11.360
Our lives will change
when tomorrow comes

41:11.480 --> 41:16.316
Tonight our hearts drown
the beating drums

41:16.440 --> 41:19.433
And we'll have music, all right

41:19.560 --> 41:21.950
Tearing the night

41:22.120 --> 41:25.477
Our song

41:25.600 --> 41:31.278
Played on a solo saxophone

41:31.400 --> 41:33.471
A crazy sound

41:33.600 --> 41:35.831
A lonely sound

41:35.960 --> 41:43.800
A cry that tells us love goes on and on

41:43.920 --> 41:49.040
Played on a solo saxophone

41:49.160 --> 41:53.473
It's telling me to hold you tight

41:53.600 --> 42:01.110
And dance like
it's the last night of the world

42:02.840 --> 42:05.992
On the other side of the Earth

42:07.200 --> 42:10.511
There's a place
your life will have worth

42:10.640 --> 42:14.077
I will take you

42:14.200 --> 42:16.396
I'll go with you

42:16.520 --> 42:20.673
You won't believe
all the things you'll see

42:20.800 --> 42:24.919
I know cos you'll see them all with me

42:25.040 --> 42:30.320
If we're together,
that's when we'll hear it again

42:30.480 --> 42:33.712
Our song

42:33.840 --> 42:38.437
Played on a solo saxophone

42:38.560 --> 42:40.836
A crazy sound

42:40.960 --> 42:42.679
A lonely sound

42:42.800 --> 42:50.435
A cry that tells us love goes on and on

42:50.560 --> 42:55.476
Played on a solo saxophone

42:55.600 --> 42:59.753
It's telling me to hold you tight

42:59.880 --> 43:06.229
And dance like
it's the last night of the world

43:06.360 --> 43:10.479
Dreams were all I ever knew

43:10.600 --> 43:14.037
Dreams you won't need when I'm through

43:14.800 --> 43:18.919
Anywhere we may be

43:19.040 --> 43:22.875
I will sing with you

43:23.000 --> 43:27.438
Our song

43:27.560 --> 43:28.994
Where are you going?

43:30.240 --> 43:32.232
(KIM SQUEALS)

43:42.960 --> 43:47.557
Played on a solo saxophone

43:47.680 --> 43:51.674
So stay with me and hold me tight

43:51.800 --> 43:55.794
And dance like it's the last night

43:55.920 --> 44:02.952
Of the world

44:22.480 --> 44:24.472
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDS AND CHEERS)

44:27.720 --> 44:29.712
(FIREWORKS)

44:33.640 --> 44:35.632
(PERCUSSION MUSIC)

45:10.040 --> 45:13.397
On silent feet it came

45:15.200 --> 45:18.557
Breathing a sheet of flame

45:18.680 --> 45:20.797
It came

45:20.920 --> 45:24.516
Closing in on its rightful prey

45:25.760 --> 45:29.197
Burning a hundred years away

45:30.400 --> 45:33.916
The morning of the dragon,
truth lit up the street

45:35.080 --> 45:38.630
The tiger we were stalking
walked on paper feet

45:40.120 --> 45:43.238
And in the clear white heat of dawn

45:44.560 --> 45:45.914
Was gone

