No, thanks, it's not my scene

01:38:04.160 --> 01:38:06.436
I can get boys from La Cage

01:38:06.560 --> 01:38:11.077
- Whatever, man. Get out of my way.
- Watch out, sir! Sir!

01:38:12.120 --> 01:38:13.918
Why is he leaving?

01:38:14.040 --> 01:38:15.394
What is that look?

01:38:15.520 --> 01:38:16.749
He was right on the hook

01:38:16.880 --> 01:38:18.837
Don't tell me he slipped free

01:38:19.520 --> 01:38:21.477
Engineer, Chris is here

01:38:21.600 --> 01:38:25.753
John is going to get him
and bring him to me

01:38:25.920 --> 01:38:28.480
My heart's ready to burst

01:38:28.600 --> 01:38:32.435
I don't know what I'll tell him first

01:38:32.560 --> 01:38:34.950
That guy is no one to trust

01:38:35.080 --> 01:38:39.313
Or a soldier who just learned
he fathered a son

01:38:39.440 --> 01:38:41.033
You got to get to Chris first

01:38:41.160 --> 01:38:44.597
I will find his address now
before he can run

01:38:44.720 --> 01:38:48.430
- Stupid
- You can trust what he'll do

01:38:48.560 --> 01:38:53.794
- Don't you worry, I'll mention you
- You'll mention me?

01:38:53.920 --> 01:38:57.550
Don't screw with me, little bitch,
I don't want any hitch

01:38:57.680 --> 01:38:59.160
You just do as you're told

01:39:00.360 --> 01:39:02.272
You go to his hotel

01:39:02.400 --> 01:39:03.675
I'll be working as well

01:39:03.800 --> 01:39:05.757
Guarding our bag of gold

01:39:06.680 --> 01:39:10.356
Tell me where and I'll go

01:39:10.480 --> 01:39:16.272
He'll be longing for me, I know

01:39:17.600 --> 01:39:19.432
You have brought me
through the lightning

01:39:19.560 --> 01:39:22.394
You have watched me from afar

01:39:25.920 --> 01:39:29.675
You know all and you forgive me

01:39:29.800 --> 01:39:32.998
Loving parents that you are

01:39:37.000 --> 01:39:38.912
- Please
- Go on, talk to your ghosts

01:39:39.040 --> 01:39:42.238
- May your daughter have your blessing
- Little girl, till you're blue

01:39:42.360 --> 01:39:45.319
On the life about to start

01:39:45.440 --> 01:39:49.150
- You have one chance, just one
- We must journey to a new world

01:39:49.280 --> 01:39:54.639
- He's here, talking to you
- This is too much for one heart

01:39:54.800 --> 01:39:56.280
I'll fix this

01:39:56.400 --> 01:39:58.119
Make yourself pretty.

01:40:28.240 --> 01:40:30.994
(WIND HOWLS)

01:40:52.040 --> 01:40:59.038
Did you think I'd gone away?

01:40:59.160 --> 01:41:05.794
I am the man you killed that day

01:41:05.920 --> 01:41:12.156
Cold, with a bullet inside my chest

01:41:12.280 --> 01:41:15.751
My corpse may be sleeping

01:41:15.920 --> 01:41:20.915
But my soul won't rest

01:41:21.040 --> 01:41:24.351
I'm the crime that you hid

01:41:24.480 --> 01:41:29.600
You can try,
but you'll never forget what you did

01:41:29.720 --> 01:41:36.559
You will never be free

01:41:36.680 --> 01:41:42.836
Not as long as there's me

01:41:44.440 --> 01:41:48.957
Did you think you would escape
the judgment that was planned?

01:41:49.120 --> 01:41:53.637
Did you think you would escape
the truth's avenging hand?

01:41:53.760 --> 01:41:58.152
Just because you have escaped
the boundaries of your land?

01:41:58.280 --> 01:42:00.033
I'm here (ECHOES)

01:42:00.160 --> 01:42:02.356
I'm here, I'm never dead!

01:42:02.480 --> 01:42:06.633
I'm here,
I am the guilt inside your head

01:42:08.000 --> 01:42:14.315
You think
your Marine's not like other men

01:42:14.480 --> 01:42:16.517
He betrayed you once

01:42:16.640 --> 01:42:20.793
And he will again

01:42:20.920 --> 01:42:23.480
Think about that night

01:42:23.600 --> 01:42:29.597
Where was he back then?

01:42:29.720 --> 01:42:31.279
I'm getting you out! Let's go!

01:42:39.000 --> 01:42:41.196
Sorry, Sergeant, as things degenerate

01:42:41.320 --> 01:42:44.074
All I'm giving her
are her emigration papers

01:42:44.200 --> 01:42:45.395
Without the wait

01:42:45.520 --> 01:42:46.920
- Sign here
- Bullshit

01:42:47.040 --> 01:42:49.077
SOLDIER:
This'll get her on board the carrier

01:42:49.200 --> 01:42:51.351
You're declaring that you will marry her

01:42:51.480 --> 01:42:53.631
When you get back to the States

01:42:53.760 --> 01:42:55.114
Sign here, come on

01:42:55.240 --> 01:42:57.232
MARINES: By order of the old man

01:42:57.360 --> 01:43:00.398
The embassy will close according to plan

01:43:00.520 --> 01:43:02.512
I'll stretch a couple of rules
to issue her pass

01:43:02.640 --> 01:43:04.080
- Thank you
- That's it, you're ready

01:43:04.200 --> 01:43:05.919
Nice ass, you're next

01:43:06.040 --> 01:43:08.077
MARINES: By order of the old man

01:43:08.240 --> 01:43:10.471
We're processing the gooks
as fast as we can

01:43:10.600 --> 01:43:13.559
I mean Vietnamese,
hey, don't get me wrong

01:43:13.680 --> 01:43:17.356
Can't save these looks for the Cong,
right? Get in there

01:43:18.760 --> 01:43:21.434
Christ, I'm due at the embassy,
no time to lose

01:43:21.560 --> 01:43:23.916
I don't want you to leave me today

01:43:24.040 --> 01:43:26.635
Well, at least Uncle Sam
bought our honeymoon cruise

01:43:26.800 --> 01:43:30.316
- If you're going, I don't want to stay
- Look, I'm leaving my gun

01:43:30.440 --> 01:43:33.717
- We've got time, stay and pack
- I will do whatever you say

01:43:33.840 --> 01:43:35.877
I'll get plenty of word
when the VC attack

01:43:36.000 --> 01:43:39.232
I want you in that bed waiting
when I get back

01:43:39.360 --> 01:43:43.718
Sorry, Sergeant, we must accelerate,
State Department says we evacuate

01:43:43.840 --> 01:43:46.799
The word is, we must be out by dawn

01:43:46.920 --> 01:43:49.389
Sorry, Sergeant,
it's straight from Washington

01:43:49.520 --> 01:43:51.512
No one leaves the grounds now,
not anyone

01:43:51.640 --> 01:43:54.599
As fast as we load the planes,
we're gone, go!

01:43:55.480 --> 01:43:57.517
OK, keep quiet, don't shout

01:43:57.640 --> 01:44:00.439
The ambassador won't leave
till everyone's out

01:44:00.560 --> 01:44:03.394
The choppers are on their way
have room for you all

01:44:03.520 --> 01:44:05.830
They're climbing over the wall

01:44:05.960 --> 01:44:08.077
Get back, get back,
I tell you, don't shout

01:44:08.200 --> 01:44:10.795
The ambassador won't leave
till everyone's out

01:44:10.920 --> 01:44:13.992
The ambassador
just sent an order to freeze

01:44:14.120 --> 01:44:17.511
That's it, no more Vietnamese, get in

01:44:17.640 --> 01:44:19.120
Lock the gates

01:44:19.240 --> 01:44:21.960
I'm the wife of a soldier,
please let me through

01:44:23.480 --> 01:44:27.599
Wait, help me, who must I pay?
Tell me what I must do

01:44:27.720 --> 01:44:29.518
- Chris!
- Let me out

01:44:29.640 --> 01:44:32.235
- No!
- I've got to get back for my bride

01:44:33.280 --> 01:44:37.638
No, listen, someone,
my husband is waiting inside

01:44:39.400 --> 01:44:44.077
Please, Kim, hear the phone

01:44:44.200 --> 01:44:46.635
I can't get there

01:44:46.800 --> 01:44:48.871
Please be home

01:44:49.000 --> 01:44:51.595
Please, Chris

01:44:51.760 --> 01:44:56.755
No one sees I am lost here

01:44:56.880 --> 01:44:58.758
Find me, please

01:44:58.880 --> 01:45:01.554
BOTH: Please get me through,
I don't care how

01:45:01.680 --> 01:45:05.151
Don't take my love away, not now

01:45:05.280 --> 01:45:11.277
- Oh, Chris, I can't get free
- Please get free

01:45:11.400 --> 01:45:13.960
- Still I'm with you
- CHRIS: I am with you

01:45:15.120 --> 01:45:18.352
BOTH: Wait for me

01:45:18.480 --> 01:45:21.279
Sorry, Sergeant, inside the embassy

01:45:21.400 --> 01:45:24.598
We are pulling out now
and there will be no more reprieves

01:45:24.720 --> 01:45:26.916
I've got till the old man leaves

01:45:27.040 --> 01:45:30.477
Chris, don't be an ass!
The ambassador is leaving now

01:45:32.200 --> 01:45:35.079
- Take me with you
- Take my children

01:45:35.200 --> 01:45:37.840
- I have a letter here
- I helped the CIA

01:45:37.960 --> 01:45:40.520
CHORUS: They'll kill who they find here

01:45:40.640 --> 01:45:43.109
Don't leave us behind here

01:45:43.240 --> 01:45:45.550
I've a wife who left already

01:45:45.680 --> 01:45:47.080
I have an aunt in New York

01:45:47.200 --> 01:45:48.554
I have gold, I can pay

01:45:48.680 --> 01:45:50.876
CHORUS: There is no one to find here

01:45:51.000 --> 01:45:53.560
They have left us behind here

01:45:53.680 --> 01:45:56.320
I must get in there, listen, anyone

01:45:56.440 --> 01:45:58.432
Please tell my husband,
look, I have his gun

01:45:58.560 --> 01:46:00.438
Out of my way
if that's all that you've got

01:46:00.560 --> 01:46:03.314
If I am here when they come,
I'll be shot

01:46:04.000 --> 01:46:05.480
(SCREAMING)

01:46:05.600 --> 01:46:07.592
Let me go, John, I can't leave her

01:46:07.720 --> 01:46:10.952
Why in the world
should I be saved instead of her?

01:46:11.080 --> 01:46:13.515
CHORUS: They'll kill who they find here

01:46:13.640 --> 01:46:15.597
Don't leave us behind here

01:46:15.760 --> 01:46:18.719
- Get off!
- It's not you, it's war that's cruel

01:46:18.840 --> 01:46:21.674
And if some dreams get smashed,
perhaps it's best they were

01:46:21.800 --> 01:46:24.235
CHORUS: There is no one to find here

01:46:24.360 --> 01:46:26.670
They have left us behind here

01:46:26.800 --> 01:46:29.360
Wake up, my friend,
your mercy trip has failed

01:46:29.480 --> 01:46:31.711
There's nothing you can do,
that ship has sailed

01:46:31.840 --> 01:46:34.230
She's not the only one
we'll have betrayed

01:46:34.360 --> 01:46:37.239
CHORUS: Get to the roof
or else we are betrayed

01:46:38.680 --> 01:46:40.876
KIM: Oh, Chris

01:46:41.000 --> 01:46:43.674
I still believe

01:46:43.800 --> 01:46:49.114
The heart of you is here with me

01:46:49.240 --> 01:46:57.239
My heart against all odds holds still

01:46:57.920 --> 01:46:59.912
(PANICKED SHOUTING)

01:47:02.560 --> 01:47:04.836
(HELICOPTER APPROACHES)

01:47:07.120 --> 01:47:09.112
(SHOUTING)

01:47:16.360 --> 01:47:18.636
(ROTORS DROWN OUT SHOUTING)

01:48:02.440 --> 01:48:04.909
Kim!

01:49:10.480 --> 01:49:12.472
Please!

01:49:13.160 --> 01:49:14.879
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDS AND CHEERS)

01:50:09.400 --> 01:50:14.759
You are sunlight

01:50:14.880 --> 01:50:18.556
And I, moon

01:50:19.200 --> 01:50:24.912
Joined by the gods of fortune

01:50:26.280 --> 01:50:31.674
Midnight and high noon

01:50:32.720 --> 01:50:36.316
That's what we are

01:50:37.320 --> 01:50:40.791
How in one night

01:50:40.920 --> 01:50:47.156
Have we come so far?

01:50:48.520 --> 01:50:55.438
Outside, day starts to dawn

01:50:55.560 --> 01:51:02.000
One long nighttime has gone

01:51:02.120 --> 01:51:03.873
I feel you near

01:51:04.000 --> 01:51:05.559
I reach your place

01:51:05.720 --> 01:51:07.473
I know you're here

01:51:07.600 --> 01:51:09.956
I touch your face

01:51:10.080 --> 01:51:17.078
And our love is reborn

01:51:30.520 --> 01:51:32.955
(CHUCKLES)

01:51:33.120 --> 01:51:37.319
Brightening the sky

01:51:37.440 --> 01:51:39.796
With the flame

01:51:43.160 --> 01:51:46.198
Of love

01:51:47.560 --> 01:51:51.395
Made of

01:51:51.520 --> 01:51:56.151
Sunlight

01:51:56.280 --> 01:52:03.039
Moonlight

01:52:05.000 --> 01:52:07.560
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDS)

01:52:08.880 --> 01:52:11.031
ENGINEER: Kim. Kim.

01:52:11.200 --> 01:52:13.271
I've found Chris. He's at this hotel.

01:52:13.400 --> 01:52:16.438
Go! I'll take care of Tam.
Don't screw this up.

01:52:17.440 --> 01:52:18.440
Yes!

01:52:20.320 --> 01:52:22.312
(ANIMATED CHATTER)

01:52:46.040 --> 01:52:47.040
Oh!

01:52:47.160 --> 01:52:50.517
- I'm sorry.
- Don't turn the bed yet, thank you.

01:52:51.880 --> 01:52:55.840
- I'm not the maid.
- Oh. Well, how can I help you?

01:52:57.760 --> 01:52:59.672
- 317?
- Yes.

01:52:59.800 --> 01:53:01.678
Christopher Scott's room?

01:53:02.920 --> 01:53:07.119
Oh, God, I see.
I know who you are.

01:53:09.280 --> 01:53:11.192
You must be Kim

01:53:11.320 --> 01:53:15.314
- Chris went to find you
- (LAUGHS)

01:53:15.440 --> 01:53:18.114
Please come inside

01:53:18.240 --> 01:53:20.596
No one will hurt you

01:53:21.960 --> 01:53:24.316
I'm Chris's wife

01:53:25.200 --> 01:53:26.759
My name is Ellen.

01:53:43.920 --> 01:53:47.630
In a way,
I'm glad I'm meeting you first

01:53:49.520 --> 01:53:53.594
Understand, you were only a name
till tonight

01:53:55.200 --> 01:53:59.194
I don't know how I'd feel
if our roles were reversed

01:54:01.840 --> 01:54:04.071
Tell me you are lying

01:54:04.200 --> 01:54:07.796
ELLEN: We've been married two years,
I'm sorry, it's true

01:54:07.920 --> 01:54:10.674
- He said he'd come to get me
- He said he tried to reach you

01:54:10.800 --> 01:54:14.794
- But what could he do?
- Please tell me you're not married

01:54:14.920 --> 01:54:18.197
You don't know,
you can't know what I've done to be here

01:54:18.320 --> 01:54:20.960
You don't know how he needed a new start

01:54:21.120 --> 01:54:24.511
I feel walls in my heart closing in

01:54:24.640 --> 01:54:28.714
I can't breathe, I can't win

01:54:31.080 --> 01:54:33.879
And your child, you say it's Chris's

01:54:35.680 --> 01:54:40.675
Oh, yes, madame, my son is Chris's

01:54:41.360 --> 01:54:44.558
I had a dream for my son to belong

01:54:44.680 --> 01:54:47.149
Not live his life in the street
like a rat

01:54:47.280 --> 01:54:50.352
We aren't rich,
but we'll give what we can

01:54:50.480 --> 01:54:54.030
Chris and I are totally together on that

01:54:54.840 --> 01:54:56.957
Then you must take Tam with you

01:54:57.080 --> 01:54:59.276
Take a child from his mother?
Impossible, Kim

01:55:00.040 --> 01:55:02.111
You must take Tam with you

01:55:02.240 --> 01:55:04.436
Then he'll get what I wanted for him

01:55:04.560 --> 01:55:06.756
But, Kim, your child needs you

01:55:06.920 --> 01:55:09.435
Chris is married to me,
we want kids of our own

01:55:09.560 --> 01:55:12.792
Tam's chance lies with you now,
not with me

01:55:12.920 --> 01:55:15.799
- Please
- No, it won't work

01:55:15.920 --> 01:55:19.516
He's your child, he's not mine

01:55:19.680 --> 01:55:23.196
If you're saying that
because you made him change his mind

01:55:23.320 --> 01:55:26.711
Chris must go away
and leave me and his son behind

01:55:26.840 --> 01:55:29.912
If you're saying that
because my husband has another wife

01:55:30.040 --> 01:55:34.080
My child has no future
like the dust of life

01:55:34.200 --> 01:55:38.831
Chris must come tonight to my place,
tell me so to my face

01:55:38.960 --> 01:55:40.758
Kim! Kim!

01:55:43.760 --> 01:55:46.229
Chris

01:55:46.360 --> 01:55:48.033
Why aren't you here now?

01:55:49.960 --> 01:55:54.477
I don't understand,
I really need you here

01:55:55.560 --> 01:55:57.119
Please

01:55:58.120 --> 01:56:00.954
Please, help me

01:56:03.640 --> 01:56:06.553
Am I fooling myself

01:56:06.680 --> 01:56:11.755
If I've already lost you?

01:56:13.280 --> 01:56:15.840
Nothing's changed, you're still mine

01:56:15.960 --> 01:56:21.194
We can try to ignore this

01:56:22.360 --> 01:56:26.912
But if she has come back in your life

01:56:27.080 --> 01:56:33.873
Well, then maybe you were never mine

01:56:34.000 --> 01:56:40.520
And yet my heart cries maybe

01:56:40.680 --> 01:56:43.149
It's a trick, it's a lie

01:56:43.280 --> 01:56:48.992
She's just trying to use you

01:56:49.120 --> 01:56:51.351
But I looked in her eyes

01:56:51.520 --> 01:56:56.151
It could kill her to lose you

01:56:56.320 --> 01:57:00.155
And maybe

01:57:00.320 --> 01:57:06.590
Just maybe you need her, too

01:57:07.560 --> 01:57:11.952
Back when we met
you were broken and wild

01:57:12.080 --> 01:57:17.030
And I held you at night
and I ached when you cried

01:57:17.160 --> 01:57:21.439
But despite what we lacked
we tried staying on track

01:57:21.560 --> 01:57:23.995
No regret

01:57:25.520 --> 01:57:32.313
Yet maybe

01:57:32.480 --> 01:57:40.035
It was fate
that suddenly brought her back to you

01:57:40.160 --> 01:57:47.795
And your love was true love
before I even knew you

01:57:47.920 --> 01:57:53.996
If the life of your dreams
is the life she is giving

01:57:54.120 --> 01:58:01.596
Should I be the one
to stop your dream from living?

01:58:01.760 --> 01:58:09.600
If you're hers, then be hers
and forget about me now

01:58:09.960 --> 01:58:12.031
I've been blind for so long

01:58:12.160 --> 01:58:16.951
But perhaps I can see now

01:58:17.080 --> 01:58:20.437
And maybe

01:58:20.560 --> 01:58:24.759
Just maybe

01:58:24.880 --> 01:58:32.356
I'll find the strength
I need to set you free now

01:58:32.480 --> 01:58:34.631
I'll be strong, I'll stand firm

01:58:34.760 --> 01:58:40.438
So my tears won't betray me

01:58:40.560 --> 01:58:44.918
But my heart might just break

01:58:46.840 --> 01:58:50.231
If what may be

01:58:50.360 --> 01:58:57.392
May be

01:59:01.600 --> 01:59:03.592
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDS AND CHEERS)

01:59:14.920 --> 01:59:16.798
We couldn't find her anywhere

01:59:16.960 --> 01:59:19.236
Honey, what's wrong?

01:59:19.360 --> 01:59:21.829
Kim was here;
the one who had to tell her was me

01:59:23.520 --> 01:59:27.878
Oh, my God,
I knew we were gone too long

01:59:28.000 --> 01:59:31.391
No, I think
it's exactly what I had to see

01:59:31.520 --> 01:59:34.035
You said you slept with her,
that's all you were

01:59:34.160 --> 01:59:38.040
Only one thing you left out
is that you loved her, God

01:59:38.160 --> 01:59:40.550
Yes, we were in love,
but it was years ago

01:59:40.680 --> 01:59:42.239
We were torn apart

01:59:42.400 --> 01:59:44.631
Don't explain,
there's nothing you can say

01:59:44.760 --> 01:59:48.515
It's like she's gone insane,
she tried to give away her own child

01:59:48.640 --> 01:59:50.279
- Ellen
- You weren't here

01:59:50.400 --> 01:59:52.471
I saw the look in her eyes,
don't you see?

01:59:52.600 --> 01:59:53.920
She thinks she is married to you

01:59:54.080 --> 01:59:55.520
- What?
- You must tell her she's not

01:59:55.640 --> 01:59:58.838
She must hear it from you!
Course, it only depends if it's true

01:59:59.000 --> 02:00:02.038
Hey, don't you doubt me, Ellen

02:00:02.160 --> 02:00:04.152
You're my wife

02:00:05.320 --> 02:00:09.234
Lots of guys came back and had no life

02:00:09.360 --> 02:00:11.829
I had you

02:00:13.200 --> 02:00:14.759
Hey.

02:00:15.760 --> 02:00:19.549
You can say what you want
but she's borne you a son

02:00:19.680 --> 02:00:20.909
Ellen

02:00:21.040 --> 02:00:25.637
In your nightmares,
the name that you shouted was hers

02:00:25.760 --> 02:00:28.070
- I know
